[SN]TITLE[SN]
Much Hoole crash: Man dies as car overturns in Lancashire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has died after the car he was travelling in crashed into a hedge and overturned in Lancashire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 70-year-old, who was driving a Nissan X-Trail, was on Liverpool Road, Much Hoole at about 10:30 BST when the vehicle mounted the kerb.
The man, from Longton, was pronounced dead at the scene. The road was closed for three hours while an investigation took place.
Police appealed for people who witnessed the crash to come forward.
